<p><strong>Skills</strong> Perception +6, Religion +3</p>

<p><strong>Senses</strong> darkvision 120 ft.</p>

<p><strong>Languages</strong> Sahuagin</p>

<p><strong>Challenge</strong> 2 (450 XP)</p>

<p><strong><em>Blood Frenzy.</em></strong> The sahuagin has advantage on melee attack rolls against any creature that doesnâ€™t have all its hit points.</p>

<p><strong><em>Limited Amphibiousness.</em></strong> The sahuagin can breathe air and water, but it needs to be submerged at least once every 4 hours to avoid suffocating.</p>

<p><strong><em>Shark Telepathy.</em></strong> The sahuagin can magically command any shark within 120 feet of it, using a limited telepathy.</p>

<p><strong><em>Spellcasting.</em></strong> The sahuagin is a 6th-level spellcaster. Her spellcasting ability is Wisdom (spell save DC 12, +4 to hit with spell attacks). She has the following cleric spells prepared:</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>Cantrips (at will): guidance, thaumaturgy</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>1st level (4 slots): bless, detect magic, guiding bolt</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>2nd level (3 slots): hold person, spiritual weapon (trident)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>3rd level (3 slots): mass healing word, tongues</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Actions</strong></p>

<p><strong><em>Multiattack.</em></strong> The sahuagin makes two melee attacks: one with her bite and one with her claws.</p>

<p><strong><em>Bite.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +3 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 3 (1d4 + 1) piercing damage.</p>

<p><strong><em>Claws.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +3 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 3 (1d4 + 1) slashing damage.</p>

